cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.NE 

The paper describes an image compression method that uses convolutional neural networks and stochastic gradient descent to optimize for rate-distortion performance. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including computer vision (cs.CV), multimedia (cs.MM), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). However, given the focus on image compression and the use of convolutional neural networks, cs.CV and cs.MM are the most likely sub-categories.
